379
00:24:42,931 --> 00:24:44,775
Rym: So imagine watching a Counter-Strike tournament.

380
00:24:44,835 --> 00:24:51,990
Rym: where Counter-Strike existed, people who had never seen it before played it live once, and then could never play it again.

381
00:24:53,070 --> 00:25:05,068
Rym: So designing games around game shows is a really interesting challenge, like I said, and unlike most of our shows about these kinds of general topics, can't really make a wide pronouncement about whether or not they're good or bad.

382
00:25:05,088 --> 00:25:06,690
Rym: Like, it's a really mixed bag.

383
00:25:06,790 --> 00:25:08,454
Scott: Some of them are great and some of them are awful.

384
00:25:08,594 --> 00:25:15,730
Scott: Even with the same exact game show, right, there's a huge variance in quality of the product, whether it's video or tabletop.

385
00:25:16,110 --> 00:25:16,210
